modules.description: Generates and manipulates 128-bit identifiers with 1.21e+24 unique values per millisecond, supporting lexicographic sorting and canonical 26-character string encoding. Functions include parsing from and converting to byte arrays, validating format, and generating time-based unique identifiers. Used in distributed systems for high-frequency, sortable, and compact unique ID generation.

Encodes UNIX timestamps and random integers into Base32 strings, increments Base32-encoded values, and generates ULIDs with optional seeding and PRNG customization. Works with integers, Base32 strings, and PRNG functions. Used to create unique, sortable identifiers for distributed systems and logging.
